description: Keep code comments minimal — only for non-obvious business/app rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Minimal Comments

Write self-explanatory code. Do NOT narrate what the code does.

Only add a comment when it explains something the code cannot:
- a non-obvious business rule or domain constraint
- a deliberate trade-off, workaround, or gotcha
- why an unusual approach was chosen

## Avoid

```ts
// Import the module
import { x } from "./x"

// Set the state to en
const [locale, setLocale] = useState("en")

// Loop over items and render them
items.map((i) => <Row key={i.id} {...i} />)
```

## Acceptable

```ts
// LinkedIn relationship lines include a leading date; keep context, drop the date.
function stripRelationshipDate(text: string) { ... }

// Skip Playwright download on Vercel (saves ~300MB per deploy).
postinstall: "[ -z \"$VERCEL\" ] && playwright install chromium || true"
```

When in doubt, leave it out. Prefer clear names over comments.
